[[File:47 and 49 Front St whole view.jpg|thumbnail|left|49 Front St. is the white building to the left; 47 Front St. is the red building to the right of the image.]]
The '''Dixon Building''' (number 49) and '''Griffiths Building''' (number 47) are parts of a heritage building located on Front Street, [[Toronto]], Ontario. The three-and-a-half storey building is an example of [[Second Empire architecture]] and was constructed in 1872-3 according to the designs of [[Walter Strickland (architect)|Walter Strickland]]. 
[[File:47 Front St roof detail.jpg|thumbnail|left|Detail of the roof window at 47 Front St.]]
The building is thought to be one of the few remaining structures in Ontario with a cast iron facade.<ref>{{cite web|title=47 Front Street, Toronto|url=http://www.historicplaces.ca/en/rep-reg/place-lieu.aspx?id=8837|work=|publisher=Historic Places.ca|month= | year=  2013 |accessdate= 2013-09-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=49 Front Street, Toronto|url=http://www.historicplaces.ca/en/rep-reg/place-lieu.aspx?id=8838|work=|publisher=Historic Places.ca|month= | year=  2013 |accessdate= 2013-09-01}}</ref> The facade of the building is protected by an [[Ontario Heritage Trust]] conservation easement. The property is also designated by the City of Toronto under Part IV of the Ontario Heritage Act (By-law 429-78).<ref>{{cite web|title=City of Toronto, Heritage Property Detail|url=http://app.toronto.ca/HeritagePreservation/details.do?folderRsn=2435205&propertyRsn=211421|work=|publisher=City of Toronto|month= | year=  2013 |accessdate= 2013-09-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=City of Toronto, Heritage Property Detail|url=http://app.toronto.ca/HeritagePreservation/details.do?folderRsn=2435206&propertyRsn=211422|work=|publisher=City of Toronto|month= | year=  2013 |accessdate= 2013-09-01}}</ref>

