{{Orphan|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox person | name = Mikael Jalving | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1968|10|1|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Aarhus]], Denmark | nationality = Danish | alma_mater = [[European University Institute]] | other_names = | occupation = {{Flatlist | *Journalist *historian *author *political commentator }} }}
'''Mikael Jalving''' (born 1 October 1968)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:KBWqwM9qEpgJ:https://www.altinget.dk/christiansborg/person/mikael-jalving+&cd=8&hl=sv&ct=clnk&gl=se |title=Mikael Jalving |website=Altinget |accessdate=11 March 2018 |language=Danish}}</ref> is a Danish journalist, historian, author and political commentator. Jalving worked as a commentator for ''[[Berlingske Tidende]]'' and wrote as the newspaper's most widely read blogger, until 2009 when he was hired by ''[[Jyllands-Posten]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Reseke|first=Louise|title=Mikael Jalving går fra Berlingske til Jyllands-Posten|url=http://mediawatch.dk/Migrerede_artikler/article5163711.ece|work=MediaWatch|date=19 February 2009|language=Danish}}</ref> He has a [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D.]] in history from the [[European University Institute]] in [[Florence]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Jalving|first=Mikael|title=De uborgerlige|url=http://jalving.blogs.berlingske.dk/2008/02/04/de-uborgerlige/|work=Berlingske|date=4 February 2008|language=Danish}}</ref>
Jalving has described himself as politically being [[National liberalism|national-liberal]], [[Social conservatism|social conservative]], and more [[Right-wing politics|right-wing]] than all parties represented in the [[Folketing]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Læserne spørger: Mikael Jalving|url=http://www.information.dk/510895|work=Information|date=27 September 2014|language=Danish}}</ref> He caught attention in [[Sweden]] in 2011 for his book ''Absolut Sverige'', which according to ''[[Dagens Nyheter]]'' describes a land of "self-righteous Swedes, treacherously lulled into a social democratic dystopia of control and political correctness".<ref name="DN">{{Cite news|last=Linder|first=Lars|title=Mikael Jalving: "Absolut Sverige. En rejse i tavshedens rige"|url=http://www.dn.se/dnbok/bokrecensioner/mikael-jalving-absolut-sverige-en-rejse-i-tavshedens-rige/|work=Dagens Nyheter|date=3 March 2011|language=Swedish}}</ref> The book was partly a response to a book by Swedish journalist [[Lena Sundström]] that criticised Danish attitudes towards immigration.<ref name="DN"/>
During the month of July 2014, Jalving hosted a limited daily radio show called ''Danmarks Röst'' ("Voice of Denmark", inspired by [[Cold War]]-era ''[[Voice of America]]''), which aimed to transmit debate to Swedish listeners about subjects perceived to be taboo in Swedish public debate.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Radio24syv laver program til svenskerne|url=http://journalisten.dk/radio24syv-laver-program-til-svenskerne|work=Journalisten.dk|date=16 June 2014|language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Danmarks Röst|url=http://www.radio24syv.dk/programmer/danmarks-roest/|work=Radio24syv|language=Danish, Swedish}}</ref>
Jalving was criticised by an [[Islam]] researcher at the [[University of Copenhagen]] for misinforming about a muslim's replies about '[[sharia]]' in a questioner that did not mention sharia, but rules in the [[Quran]], while sharia are based on other texts.<ref>Karoline Rahbek Juncker & Jakob Bang Schmidt 26. FEB. 2015 Faktatjek: Debat om radikale muslimer er fuld af fejl. News and Detektor, DR (Danish Radio). https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/faktatjek-debat-om-radikale-muslimer-er-fuld-af-fejl. Seen 23-07-2017</ref>
