{{Infobox book | name = Points...: Interviews, 1974–1994 | title_orig = Points de suspension. Entretiens | translator = [[Peggy Kamuf]] | image = File:Points, French edition.jpg | caption = Cover of the first edition | author = [[Jacques Derrida]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = France | language = French | series = | subject = [[Philosophy]] | publisher = Éditions Galilée | release_date = 1992 | english_release_date = 1995 | media_type = Print | pages = 499 (English translation) | isbn = 0-8047-2488-1 | dewey= | congress= | oclc= | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Points...: Interviews, 1974–1994''''' ({{lang-fr|Points de suspension. Entretiens}}) is a 1995 book collecting interviews by the French philosopher [[Jacques Derrida]]. It contains the translation of all the interview of the 1992 French edition, plus two additional interviews, ''Honoris Causa'' (on Cambridge granting him the honorary doctorate) and "The Work of Intellectuals and the Press".
